public interface TypeNativeObject
extends TypeNative

The TypeNativeObject is the interface that represents a native type declaration of Object based classes: "can be native" and native capable classes (predefined and user defined).

Method Detail

newValue

java.lang.Object newValue()
Returns a new instance of the class used to declare the native type.

For instance: if java.lang.String was used to declare this native type, the returned object is a empty java.lang.String.

The object is created with a normal new, without reflection (except the first instance used as factory and multidimensional arrays).

It native type was declared using a native class, the returned object is native capable but is not made native, to make native use NativeManager.makeNative(Object).

Returned wrapper objects of "can be native" objects are usually incompleted, set a value with NativeSingleFieldContainer.setValue(Object) before make native.

Returns:
the new object.
